Fast-rising Ugandan singer Martha Mukisa, 25, has announced she is about to release her debut EP, 'International Local'. She said in a statement, "It is expected to be a crossover project to the continent and east Africa as a whole." Mukisa has cited her mentors as Whitney Houston, Beyonce, Tiwa Savage, Wizkid, Juliana Kanyomozi and John Blaq. The vocalist grew up in a religious setting and started her singing career in church at an early age. She is a graduate with a diploma in textile designing and technology from Kyambogo University. Her music career took an upswing when she signed to Black Magic Entertainment, a record label known to be producing the biggest brands in the industry.